= Guide - Creating global hotkeys with EventGhost =

In order for this guide to be useful the following softwares are needed:
  * EventGhost
  * [wiki:"EventGhost plugin"]

---

== Procedure ==

'''1. Start EventGhost.'''

[[Image(Hotkey1.png)]]

'''2. Add plugin, click "Keyboard" under "Remote receiver".'''

'''3. Add plugin, click "TellStick" under "External Haedware Control".'''

[[Image(Hotkey1b.png)]]

'''4. Create a new macro ("Add macro"), choose an event, for example TellStick - turn on.'''

[[Image(Hotkey2.png)]]

'''5. Choose which unit to control.'''

[[Image(Hotkey3.png)]]

'''6. Uncheck "Log only assigned and activated events".'''

[[Image(Hotkey4.png)]]

'''5. Press the button combination you want to connect to the macro.'''

[[Image(Hotkey5.png)]]

'''5. Pull the button combination from the log-window to the left to the macro.'''

[[Image(Hotkey6.png)]]

'''6. Test the macro by pressing the button combination.'''